algorithm_technique: Breadth-First Search (BFS) starting from single digits to generate sequential numbers.
Pre-generating all sequential numbers and filtering them based on the range.
problem_summary_simple: Find all numbers within a range that have digits increasing sequentially by one.
problem_summary_technical: Generates sequential digit numbers using BFS and filters them based on the given low and high bounds.
key_insights: The number of sequential digit numbers is very small and finite (at most 9 + 8 + ... + 1 = 45).
A BFS approach starting from single digits (1-9) is efficient for generating these numbers in increasing order.
The generation process can be thought of as building numbers by appending the next sequential digit.
The constraint `num % 10 + 1 < 10` ensures that we don't generate numbers with digits like 910.
